Neptunium is found in three forms (Donohue, 1974): \begin{itemize} \item The ground state, \href{current_web_home_dir/A_oP8_62_2c-001}{$\alpha$-Np ($A_{c}$)}, stable below 280$^\circ$C, (this structure) \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A_tP4_129_ac-001}{$\beta$-Np ($A_{d}$)}, stable in the range 280-577$^\circ$C, and \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A_cI2_229_a-001}{a body-centered cubic ($A2$)} structure above 577$^\circ$C. \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-.25in} 
 (Zachariasen, 1952) describes this structure using the $Pmcn$ setting of space group \#62.  We transformed this to the standard $Pnma$ setting. 
  \href{current_web_home_dir/A_oP8_62_2c-001}{$\alpha$-Np} and \href{current_web_home_dir/A_oP8_62_2c-002}{high-pressure orthorhombic Na} have the same AFLOW prototype label, A\_oP8\_62\_2c. They are generated by the same symmetry operations with different sets of parameters ({\tt --params}) specified in their corresponding CIF files.
